headline: Samsung to start production of HBM4 chips next month for Nvidia supply, source says
summary: Samsung Electronics plans to ​start production of ‌its next-generation high-bandwidth memory (HBM) chips, or ‌HBM4, starting next month and supply them to Nvidia, a person ⁠familiar with ‌the matter told Reuters on Monday. The person ‍declined to give details such as how many chips ​it plans to supply ‌to Nvidia. A Samsung spokesperson declined to comment.
